From 1584b1a06d9ddd10564fa564bda027df373b054f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Phoenix-RTOS RPi4 port <witold.bolt@jit.team>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 00:34:45 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 16/17] v3d: Phoenix-RTOS RPi4 port (BCM2711 V3D 4.2 GL)

Phoenix-RTOS bring-up edits for the V3D 4.2 gallium driver + GL frontend on the
Raspberry Pi 4 (BCM2711), on top of upstream e8791b4bc1c (26.1-branchpoint-2792).

- v3d gallium: uncached/contiguous BO alloc via Phoenix mmap + va2pa, SLCACTL
  per-submit, EZ handling, flat page-table plumbing (v3d_bufmgr, v3d_context,
  v3d_resource, v3dx_draw, v3dx_state).
- state_tracker: st_atom_framebuffer Phoenix scanout adjustments.
- util: blake3 BLAKE3_USE_NEON=0 (no runtime NEON detect on Phoenix);
  os_memory_aligned Phoenix aligned-alloc shim.

HW-proven: clear -> textured triangle -> tumbling cube -> GLQuake on the real
V3D 4.2 (in-process winsys, self-powered V3D). Upstream pin e8791b4 is no longer
fetchable from gitlab (main advanced); this branch preserves the exact validated
tree so the build is reproducible from our fork.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
